'''1885年塔科马排華事件'''（{{lang-en|1885 Chinese expulsion from Tacoma}}），也称'''1885年塔科马暴乱'''（Tacoma riot of 1885）是一个[[种族清洗|种族清洗]]的[[反华|反华]]事件，发生于1885年11月3日，在[[塔科马_(华盛顿州)|塔科马]]当时的[[唐人街|唐人街]]<ref name="Pfaelzer">{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/214322891|publisher=University of California Press|date=2008|location=Berkeley|isbn=978-0-520-25694-1|oclc=214322891|first=Jean|last=Pfaelzer|title=Driven out : the forgotten war against Chinese Americans}}</ref><ref name=Jean>{{cite book|last1=菲尔泽|first1=琼|date=2016-08-01|title=驱逐(被遗忘的美国排华战争)|url=http://www.zxhsd.com/kgsm/ts/2016/10/10/3654114.shtml|pages=431|publisher=花城|isbn=9787536080508}}</ref>。

数日之内唐人的建筑物也都被烧毁，此后塔科马就再没有唐人街了<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SQPRCA9S9WAC|title=Asian American Chronology: Chronologies of the American Mosaic|last1=Zhao|first1=Xiaojian|year=2009|pages=147|isbn=9780313348754|publisher=Greenwood Press|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2016-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405084809/https://books.google.com/books?id=SQPRCA9S9WAC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==背景==
[[File:Tacoma_Pac_Ave_1885.jpg|thumb]]
19世纪中期華人开始移民到美国西部从事于矿工与[[第一条横贯大陆铁路|铁路]]等[[苦力|苦力]]工作<ref>{{cite news|last=Sayej|first=Nadja|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/jul/18/forgotten-by-society-how-chinese-migrants-built-the-transcontinental-railroad|title='Forgotten by society' – how Chinese migrants built the transcontinental railroad|date=2019-07-18|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511161207/https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/jul/18/forgotten-by-society-how-chinese-migrants-built-the-transcontinental-railroad|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.history.com/news/transcontinental-railroad-chinese-immigrants|title=Building the Transcontinental Railroad: How 20,000 Chinese Immigrants Made It Happen|last1=Kennedy|first1=Lesley|date=2019-05-10|publisher=A&E Television Networks, LLC.|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526135325/https://www.history.com/news/transcontinental-railroad-chinese-immigrants|dead-url=no}}</ref>。那时期华工在美国受到相当大的偏见与排斥，很多白人认为华人的低价勞力会压低他们自己的工资或抢他们的工作<ref name="Morgan">{{cite book|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/j.ctvcwn271|title=Puget's Sound: A Narrative of Early Tacoma and the Southern Sound
|last=Morgan|first=Murray|publisher=University of Washington Press|year=1981|isbn=0295958421}}</ref><ref name="Lang">{{cite book|last1=Morgan|first1=Murray|last2=Lang|first2=William L.|date=2003|title=Puget's Sound: A Narrative of Early Tacoma and the Southern Sound|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ufZMHQAACAAJ|publisher=University of Washington Press|isbn=0295983035|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2014-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111141257/http://books.google.com/books?id=ufZMHQAACAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Cross>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/historyoflabormo00cros|first=Ira|last=Cross|chapter=VII: 'The Chinese Must Go'|date=1935|title=A History of the Labor Movement in California|publisher=University of California Press
|location=Berkeley, California|pages=88–129|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/historyoflabormo00cros/page/88/mode/2up
}}</ref>{{rp|88}}。

从1873年开始，美国进入一个长期的[[w:Long_Depression|经济衰退]]。美国工人对“中国佬”的偏见也更加高，[[美国反中情绪|美国反中情绪]]也越激烈<ref name="Boomtown-1">{{Cite web|title=Boomtown, 1870s: Decade of Bonanza, Bust and Unbridled Racism|url=https://www.kqed.org/news/10413670/draft-boomtown-history-2a|accessdate=2021-03-26|author=Dan Brekke|date=2015-02-11|work=KQED|language=|archive-date=2021-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502174528/https://www.kqed.org/news/10413670/draft-boomtown-history-2a|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

1873年底，{{Le|北太平洋铁路|Northern Pacific Railway}}在塔科马的终點站竣工。很多铁路[[华工|华工]]便在附近的水滨工业找工作<ref name="Hildebrand">{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/3759768|publisher=Washington State American Revolution Bicentennial Commission|date=1977|location=Tacoma|isbn=0-917048-05-9|oclc=3759768|last=Hildebrand|first=Lorraine|title=Straw hats, sandals, and steel : the Chinese in Washington State}}</ref>，並於塔科马車站附近形成唐人街，當時又有「小广州」（Little Canton）之稱，即今塔科马市中心东部海灣岸边<ref name="community">{{Cite web|title=Little Canton|url=https://www.tacomamethod.com/chinese-community|accessdate=2021-03-26|work=The Tacoma Method|language=|archive-date=2021-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210521043217/https://www.tacomamethod.com/chinese-community|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/golden-tassels-a-history-of-the-chinese-in-washington-1857-1977/oclc/3240796|publisher=Chin|date=1977|location=Seattle|oclc=3240796|language=|first=Art|last=Chin|title=Golden tassels: a history of the Chinese in Washington, 1857-1977}}</ref>。

[[1877年三藩市反华暴乱|1877年三藩市反华暴乱]]之后，{{Le|加州工人工会|Workingmen's Party of California}}於[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]成立，該工會特别强调反对华人劳工，甚至以「華人必須滾！」（''The Chinese must go!''）為組織口号<ref>{{cite book|author1=Huping Ling|author2=Allan W. Austin|title=Asian American History and Culture: An Encyclopedia: An Encyclopedia
|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OvBnBwAAQBAJ&pg=PT1346|date=2015-03-17|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-317-47644-3}}</ref>。此口号传遍美国西部，塔科马也用以此激起当地的[[反华|排華]]運動<ref name="Hildebrand"/>。無獨有偶地，另一个工会「{{Le|勞動騎士團|Knights of Labor}}」在[[华盛顿州|华盛顿州]]利用[[反华|反华]]情绪，来促进白人劳工的利益<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JImlIbueaXcC|title=The Pacific Northwest|last=Schwantes|first=Carlos|publisher=University of Nebraska Press|date=Jan 1, 1996|isbn=9780803292284|pages=335–336|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2016-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022092211/https://books.google.com/books?id=JImlIbueaXcC|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

1882年[[美国国会|美国国会]]通过[[美国排华法案|美国排华法案]]，停止华人移民<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?doc=47|title=An act to execute certain treaty stipulations relating to the Chinese|date=May 6, 1882|publisher=General Records of the United States Government|website=National Archive|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516142944/https://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?doc=47|dead-url=no}}</ref>。1884年一个新成立的「工人工会」（Workingmen's Union）支持一位德国移民商人雅各布·魏斯巴赫（Jacob Weisbach）当选塔科马市长<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Anti-Chinese Outbreak in Tacoma, 1885|url=https://online.ucpress.edu/phr/article/23/3/271/73950/The-AntiChinese-Outbreak-in-Tacoma-1885|last=Karlin|first=Jules Alexander|date=1954-08-01|journal=Pacific Historical Review|issue=3|doi=10.2307/3635568|volume=23|pages=271–283|language=|issn=0030-8684}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Anti-Chinese Outbreak in Tacoma, 1885|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/3635568|last=Karlin|first=Jules Alexander|date=1954|journal=Pacific Historical Review|issue=3|doi=10.2307/3635568|volume=23|pages=271–283|issn=0030-8684|access-date=2021-03-26|archive-date=2021-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114194340/https://www.jstor.org/stable/3635568|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

1885年2月，[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的[[1885年华人被逐出尤里卡|尤里卡]]将市内所有华人驱逐<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Chinese Expulsion from Humboldt County|url=https://online.ucpress.edu/phr/article/30/4/329/72526/Chinese-Expulsion-from-Humboldt-County|last=Carranco|first=Lynwood|date=1961-11-01|journal=Pacific Historical Review|issue=4|doi=10.2307/3636420|volume=30|pages=329–340|language=|issn=0030-8684}}</ref>。当时塔科马人口有6,936，其中700是華人<ref name="community" /><ref name="Wilcox">{{cite book|last=Wilcox|first=W.P.|chapter=Anti-Chinese Riots in Washington|editor-last=Daniels|editor-first=Roger|title=Anti-Chinese Violence in North America|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BX0aAQAAIAAJ
|publisher=Arno Press|date=1978|pages=204-212|isbn=0405112637}}</ref>。

==驱逐==
[[File:Anti-Chinese_Mass_Meeting_-_Tacoma_poster.jpg|thumb]]
1885年2月中旬，塔科马市长雅各布·魏斯巴赫（Jacob Weisbach）与一小群人开会，讨论「華人问题」。那时[[1885年华人被逐出尤里卡|尤里卡华人驱逐事件]]的消息刚刚传到塔科马，他们听到了这“尤里卡办法”便决定再开一些更大会议来解决此"问题"<ref name="Hunt">{{cite book|last1=Hunt|first1=Herbert|date=1916|title=Tacoma: Its History and Its Builders; a Half Century of Activity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MIEUAAAAYAAJ|publisher=S.J. Clarke Publishing Company|isbn=0972684395|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2016-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610072436/https://books.google.com/books?id=MiEuAAAAYAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{rp|359}}<ref name="Morgan"/>{{rp|222}}。

然后魏斯巴赫在阿尔法歌剧院（Alpha Opera House）召集了两次市民大会（2月21日與6月3日）<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonhistory.org/research/collection-item/?irn=87901|title=Great Anti-Chinese Mass Meeting|date=1885|publisher=Washington State Historical Society|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120204452/https://www.washingtonhistory.org/research/collection-item/?irn=87901|dead-url=no}}</ref>，决定禁止雇用华人并将华人驱逐城外<ref name="Morgan"/>{{rp|223}}。

1885年9月2日[[石泉城大屠杀|石泉城大屠杀]]爆发，9月7日{{le|史夸克谷|Attack on Squak Valley Chinese laborers, 1885}}也发生华人谋杀事件，这些新闻更加激动了塔科马的反华分子<ref name="Hunt"/>{{rp|365}}。

1885年9月28日，魏斯巴赫又在[[西雅图|西雅图]]召开了一个“反华代表会”（Anti-Chinese Congress），魏斯巴赫选为主席。这个代表会就决定将华人从整个[[华盛顿州|华盛顿州]]西部驱逐<ref name="Hunt"/>{{rp|366}}。

1885年10月3日，塔科马的阿尔法歌剧院又开了会议，选出一个十五人委员会来执行此驱逐。这十五人委员会便通知市内所有华人要以11月1日之前离开。在这威胁之下，很多华人便开始移出塔科马，但是11月1日期限过后还有约200华人留在城内<ref name="Wilcox"/>{{rp|206}}。

1885年11月3日，一群约500人的暴民与警察侵入塔科马的唐人街（共两个区域）。这群人的领导人物包括市长魏斯巴赫与两位未来的市长，共27人。后来这27人就称为“塔科马27”（Tacoma 27）。这群暴徒把唐人街全部居民强迫运到火车站，驱逐至[[波特兰_(俄勒冈州)|波特兰]]<ref name="Pfaelzer"/>{{rp|219}}<ref name="Chang">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1a7gXiXnKF0C|title=The Chinese in America: A Narrative History|last1=Chang|first1=Iris|date=Mar 30, 2004|isbn=9781101126875|pages=512|publisher=Penguin}}</ref><ref name="CSPN">{{cite web|url=https://www.washington.edu/uwired/outreach/cspn/Website/Classroom%20Materials/Pacific%20Northwest%20History/Lessons/Lesson%2015/15.html|title=Chinese and the Anti-Chinese Movement in the Late 19th-Century Northwest|publisher=University of Washington|website=Center for the Study of the Pacific Northwest|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416173040/https://www.washington.edu/uwired/outreach/cspn/Website/Classroom%20Materials/Pacific%20Northwest%20History/Lessons/Lesson%2015/15.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在此华人被迫购买自己的火车票。没钱买票的人只好坐货车的车厢，或沿着铁路走140英里到波特兰<ref name="Pfaelzer"/>{{rp|219}}。当天天气是倾盆暴雨，在火车站等车的华人有两人遭到凍死<ref name="Chang"/><ref name="Sailor">{{cite news|last=Sailor|first=Craig|url=https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/local/article236845128.html|title=Forgotten Tacoma diary reveals shameful past.|date=2019-11-04|newspaper=Tacoma News Tribune|accessdate=2021-03-25|archive-date=2019-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215050255/https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/local/article236845128.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

几天之内，这两个唐人街便遭到烧毁<ref name="Pfaelzer"/>{{rp|222}}<ref name="Hildebrand"/>{{rp|57}}，因此塔科马成為当今美国西海岸主要港都之中，唯一没有唐人街者<ref>{{cite news|last=Hanchard|first=Jenna|url=https://www.king5.com/article/news/local/tacoma-remembers-chinese-expulsion-more-than-100-years-later/281-394740727|title=Tacoma remembers Chinese expulsion more than 100 years later|date=2017-01-30|newspaper=KING-TV}}</ref>。

1885年11月7日，“塔科马27”被控告阴谋之罪，但他们一直没有被定罪。这27人成为当地的英雄，并还继续领导地方政治好几年<ref name="Sailor"/><ref name="expulsion">{{cite web|url=https://www.tacomamethod.com/expulsion|title=Expulsion - The Tacoma Method|last1=Gomez|first1=Andrew|date=2017|publisher=University of Puget Sound|access-date=2021-03-25|archive-date=2021-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210521041716/https://www.tacomamethod.com/expulsion|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Hunt"/>{{rp|383}}。
